Just a note of caution here on backing up to an external hard drive.  I had
been doing so on a regular basis.  Then, back in August, we were hit by a
very nearby lightning strike.  All my computer gear that used 120 VAC was
plugged into a surge protector.  No matter.  The lightning entered via my
broadband cable connection.  Destroyed the cable modem, wiped out the PC,
both mother board and both hard drives,  then proceeded to destroy
everything connected to the computer via USB connectors; printer, mouse,
keyboard, and of course the external back up hard drive.

So to be on the safe side, disconnect the external HD from the computer when
not actually using it.  Fortunately, I have most of my stuff also backed up
to CD-RW's, but teaching Vista to use all the programs is a PITA.

Ron K
